<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,298,524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,298,324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">Genus description.</emphasis>
Members of this genus are recognised by weakly sclerotised dorsal propodosomal areas in females and without subcuticular reticulations. In males, weakly sclerotised dorsal hysterosomal areas may be present or absent. Genital setae either three or four pairs. Palp basi- and telofemora bearing dorsal simple tactile seta. Legs usually shorter than idiosoma. All leg femora divided by articulation facets.
</paragraph>
